= LUWRAIN downloads =

== For~end~users ==

These options are purposed for~everybody who would like to~use LUWRAIN just for~the~work.
The~only difference between them is the~operating system they can be~launched on
(or~without operating system at~all 
as~in~the~case of~bootable ISO-images).

Choose the~most suitable form of~LUWRAIN distribution you need:

* [local:iso/ 
Bootable ISO-images] (installed operating system isn't needed)

* [local:windows/
For~Microsoft Windows]

* [local:linux/
For~GNU/Linux]

* [local:mac/
For~Apple Mac~OS~X]

== For~developers ==

The~first option of~this list is purposed for~the~developers
of~applications for~LUWRAIN.
Others can be~useful only for~developers who would like to~improve LUWRAIN itself.

* [local:sdk/
LUWRAIN~SDK] 
(needed for~building your own applications for~LUWRAIN)

* [local:git/
Git~repositories]
(the~entire set of~version tracking repositories with source  code of~our project)

* [tarball/
The~tarballs with source materials]
(published basically to~make LUWRAIN sources downloadable in~single click
but there is a~tarball with~media files which aren't present in~Git repositories)

{NOTE!} You may always use the~host [http://download.luwrain.org download.luwrain.org] directly 
as~a~single, easily observable place gathering all of~our~materials for~download.

